Have you seen cinnamon toast crunch minis?! They're super cute and makes these treats taste like cinnamon rolls. Absolutely delicious and super easy!

- 6 cups cinnamon toast crunch minis cereal
- 1 stick butter
- 10.5 oz bag of mini marshmallows 
- heavy pinch of salt

Melt butter in a sauce pan. Stir in salt then marshmallows into butter until melted and mixed together. Pour over cereal and mix together until fully incorporated. Spray a sheet pan or a shallow sided pan before pressing cereal mixture into it. (The bigger the pan the thinner they'll be. Use a smaller pan for thick treats.) Press cereal and let cool. Enjoy!

Warm yourself up with this garlicky chicken and vegetable soup. Tender chicken thighs and crispy skin. A bowl of warm happiness.

Chicken:
4 Skin on, bone in chicken thighs
1-2 cups Chicken stock (homemade or store bought)
3 sprigs of thyme
1 tbsp lemon zest
1 head of garlic
Olive oil
Salt/pepper

Soup:
5 celery stalks
1 large Onion
2 medium carrots, peeled
1 large bell pepper or 6 mini sweet peppers
4 cups chicken stock (homemade or store bought)
2 tbsp butter
Garlic
Salt and pepper

Preheat oven to 400⁰
Make sure to use an oven safe pan!
Trim chicken thighs to remove skin that would be on the under side. Leave the skin on top. Salt and pepper both sides of the thighs.
In a large pan heat oil to medium heat. Sear skin side down first until starting to get a little color. Flip and do the same for the bottom. 
Remove chicken. Add in garlic to your hearts desire (I'll add about 4 or 5 sliced cloves) and saute until fragrant. Add in 1 cup of chicken stock and scrape the bottom of the pan. Add your thyme and lemon zest. Place chicken back in the pan skin side up. Stock should come up about half way but not covering the thighs. Place pan in the oven for an hour or until completely tender and skin is crisp.

Dice vegetables and garlic. Sweat onions under softened. Add remaining vegetables and do the same. Add in 1 tbsp of minced garlic and stir until fragrant. Salt and pepper vegetables and stir. Add in chicken stock. Bring to a boil and then lower to a simmer while chicken cooks. 

When chicken is tender and almost fall off the bone remove to rest. Remove skin and place to the side. Pull chicken meat off the bones. 

You can mix in with the soup and ladle it all together or ladle soup into your bowl and place chicken on top. I like to do it on top and garnish with crispy chicken skin so it doesn't get soft!

Start 2023 off with these goat cheese stuffed figs. Sweet, tangy, and a little salty. Perfect little bites of happiness. 

4oz goat cheese
1-2 TBSP Milk or cream
1 TBSP thyme
½ TBSP parsley
1-2 TBSP your favorite honey
1-2 TBSP chopped pecans 
Cracked black pepper
5-8 fresh figs

In a small bowl combine your goat cheese, 1 TBSP milk or cream, thyme, parsley, and cracked pepper. Mix until combined and smooth. (Only add in the remaining TBSP of milk or cream if needed.)

Slice the stem off your figs. Without cutting all the way through carefully slice in half and in half again so you have an opening in the figs. Repeat with each fig. 

In a piping bag with the goat cheese (or a zip lock bag with a tip cut off)  fill the very center of the figs up to the tip. Finish off with a drizzle of honey and chopped pecans.

Warm yourself from the inside out with this roasted red pepper and tomato soup! Perfect with grilled cheese or toasted focaccia.

3 lbs plum tomatoes
10 oz @mezzetta roasted red peppers
½ cup heavy cream
1 small onion, diced 
1-2 tbsp minced garlic
2 tbsp chopped basil
1 tsp thyme
Salt and pepper to taste
Olive oil

Preheat oven to 375⁰. 

Slice tomatoes in half, toss with olive oil, salt/pepper, and lay out in a sheet tray. Roast tomatoes until tender. 
In a large pot, pour in some olive oil and sweat diced onions until soft. Add in minced garlic and cook until fragrant.
Drain roasted red peppers. Blend tomatoes, roasted red peppers, onions, garlic, and basil until smooth with a blender or food processor.

Add back into your pot the blended tomatoes/peppers, roasted red peppers, thyme, and heavy cream. Stir until all combined and cook until heated through. Add salt and pepper as needed.

*Note*-- you can use cans of crushed tomatoes (use cans with nothing added)

For national chocolate cake day you really want to make these cakey baked doughnuts! They're full of Nutella and chocolate and happiness. You want to save this recipe!

2 cups AP flour
½ cup cocoa powder
¾ cups granulated sugar
2 teaspoons baking powder
1 teaspoon salt
2 large eggs
½ cup Nutella 
½ cup whole milk
2 tablespoons butter melted
2 tablespoon olive oil
1½ teaspoons vanilla paste
Chopped, roasted hazelneuts

Preheat to 350⁰ and grease a doughnut pan.
Mix all ingredients together and add to a piping bag or large zip lock. Cut off the tip and pipe into the doughnut mold. 
Bake until a toothpick comes out clean.

When cooled dip the doughnuts into melted chocolate and top with hazelnuts.

*TIP* spray the inside of your measuring cup to easily get Nutella out.

Maple bacon minis! These doughnuts are sweet and salty. Everything you need!

Doughnuts:
3 ⅔ cups flour
1 teaspoon salt
2 teaspoons baking powder
¾ teaspoon baking soda
1 and 1/2 cups soft butter
2 cups brown sugar
3 large eggs
1 tsp maple extract
1 ½ cups milk

Glaze:
½ cup Powdered sugar
1 tbsp maple syrup
2-3 tbsp of milk
½ cup chopped bacon

Cream butter and sugar  until light and fluffy. Add eggs in one at a time. Scrape down the sides after each egg is incorporated.
Add milk, maple, flour, salt, baking powder and soda. Mix until just combined. Don't overmix.

Spray mini doughnut pan lightly. Pipe or spoon batter into cavity about half way up. Bake at 350⁰ until golden. (Same directions using a larger doughnut pan.) Let cool before glazing.

Mix powdered sugar, syrup and 2 tbsp of milk.  If too thick add another tbsp of milk. You want it thick enough to coat but not super runny.
Dip cooled doughnuts into glaze and top with bacon.

*Chopped walnuts or pecans are also great if you're not a bacon person.

*If your doughnuts aren't popping out easily and you have silicone pans put the qhole thing in the freezer for 30-40 minutes and you should be able to pop them out easier.

Banana bread? Chai? Pecans? If that's a yes then you definitely want to make these banana nut Chai muffins.

1½ cups flour
1 tsp baking powder
1 tsp baking soda
½ tsp salt
¾ cup brown sugar
 3-4 tbsp just egg or use 1 egg
2 tsp Chai spice
3 very ripe bananas
Chopped pecans for topping

Preheat your oven to 350⁰
Throw all the ingredients in a mixing bowl and mix in low speed until everything comes together. Spray and scoop into a loaf pan or into a muffin tin. Top muffins with chopped pecans before placing in the oven.
Bake at 350⁰ until a tooth pick or knife comes out clean. Let cool and enjoy!

*omit the pecans if you can't do nuts. Walnuts are a great sub if you don't like pecans

Our cider chicken is one of our most popular menu picks! A little sweet and garlicky. Hit save to keep this recipe!

What you need:
-skin on chicken thighs
-cider (hard cider or not, up to you!)
-½ cup chicken stock
-olive oil
-4 sprigs lemon thyme 
-3 cloves chopped garlic
-zest and juice of half a lemon
-salt and pepper

Set oven to 400⁰F
-salt, pepper, and olive oil all sides of each chicken thigh and sear them skin side down first.
-in a baking dish put garlic, lemon, and thyme
-add chicken thighs skin side up
-pour in enough cider to the dish to come half way up the thighs plus the ½ cup of stock
-place in the middle of your oven, uncovered, until the skin is golden brown and the meat is tender. 1½-2 hours 
-chicken should have a crispy skin and tender, fall off the bone meat
-use the extra cooking liquid to dip in! 😋

Skim any foam that accumulates on the surface.

You need:
6 cups hulled strawberries
4 cups fresh lemon juice
6 cups sugar

INSTRUCTIONS
Prepare a water bath canner, jars, rings, and lids before beginning. The canner should be pre-heated for hot pack.
Juice the lemons and strain to remove any pulp and seeds.
Hull and puree the strawberries.
Mix the strawberries, strained lemon juice, and sugar in a saucepan.
Gently heat the mixture on the stove to around 190 degrees F, but do not boil.
Ladle the strawberry lemonade concentrate into prepared jars, leaving 1/2 inch headspace. Seal with 2 part canning lids.
Process the jars in a water bath canner for 15 minutes, adjusting to the altitude.
Turn off the heat and leave the jars in the canner for an additional 5 minutes to cool slightly before removing them with a canning jar lifter to cool completely on a towel on the counter.
Wait 12 to 24 hours, then check seals.

To reconstitute, mix 1 part concentrate with 3 parts water.  For a 1 pint jar, you'd add 3 pints of water.

Lemon ricotta cake with limoncello! 🍋 

1 ½ sticks of soft butter
1 ½ cups of granulated sugar
15 ounces whole milk ricotta (usually the small containers are 15)
3 eggs
Zest and juice of one large lemon
½ teaspoon salt
½ teaspoon baking soda
1 ½ cups flour

Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Grease a 9 inch pan or silicone baking mold

In a large mixing bowl or stand up mixer, cream together the butter and sugar until combined. Add in the ricotta cheese and blend until light and fluffy, about 4 to 5 minutes.

Add eggs, one at a time. Then add in lemon zest and lemon juice and mix to combine. In the same bowl, stir in the baking soda and salt. Mix and scrape down the sides. Add in the flour and mix until combined

Pour the batter into your pan and bake for 45-55 minutes, or until a toothpick inserted in the middle of the cake comes out clean
For smaller cakes check after 15 minutes with a toothpick to see if it comes out clean.

Peppermint bark madeleines are exactly what you want to bring to the Christmas table. Treat yourself and your loved ones to something a little different. 🎄❤️💚 Recipe below:

9 TBSP butter
1 cup AP flour
3 TBSP cocoa powder
½ tsp baking powder
¼ tsp salt
⅔ cup granulated white sugar
2 large eggs
1 teaspoon vanilla
1 tablespoon melted butter for brushing the madeleine pan
Madeleine pan (I use silpat)

Preheat oven to 350⁰
In a small bowl, whisk together the AP flour, cocoa powder, baking powder, and salt. Set asid

Add the granulated sugar, eggs, and vanilla to a large bowl. Beat the eggs and sugar on high with an electric mixer for 3-5 minutes, or until the mixture is pale yellow and shiny

Fold in the dry ingredients until everything is combined
Melt butter and fold it in just until combined. Don't over mix the batter.

Use a pastry brush to brush melted butter into each madeleine well. Add about 1½ tablespoon of batter into each well of the buttered pan. Bake the madeleines for 9-11 minutes until they have domed. For minis, add about 1½ teaspoons to each well and then keep an eye on them. 4-6 minutes. Remove them from the oven and let them cool in their pan.

Remove madeleines from mold. Clean out the mold and fully dry it out. Using tempered chocolate, pour 1-2 teaspoons of chocolate into each cavity and gently place each madeleine back into the mold detailed side down. Let the chocolate cool and then pop the madeleines out! The chocolate will take the shape of the mold. 

For peppermint bark sprinkle crushed peppermint into the mold and then top with the tempered chocolate and repeat the above.
